<title>USA: Vertex amends shareholder rights.</title>
<headline>Vertex amends shareholder rights.</headline>
<dateline>CAMBRIDGE, Mass. 1997-02-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Vertex Pharmaceuticals Inc said Tuesday it has amended its stockholder rights plan, increasing the exercise price of the rights to $270 from $60.</p>
<p>The amendment also reduces the trigger for the rights plan to 15 percent from 20 percent.</p>
<p>Vertex said it was not amending the shareholder rights plan in response to any proposal to acquire the company.</p>
<p>Under the amended plan, if a person or group acquires or seeks to acquire 15 percent or more of Vertex's common stock, the other shareholders would be entitled to purchase Vertex shares worth twice the $270-per-share exercise price.</p>
